January 16, 2026
SENATE BILL No. 157
_____
DIGEST OF SB 157 (Updated January 14, 2026 1:03 pm - DI 154)
Citations Affected: IC 27-1.
Synopsis: Disclosures related to prescription drugs. Requires a
pharmacist or pharmacy to provide the amount of the national average
drug acquisition cost for a generic drug on the written materials
provided to an individual at the point of sale of the generic drug.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Bohacek, Jackson L,
Randolph Lonnie M
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Insurance and Financial
Institutions.
January 15, 2026, amended, reported favorably — Do Pass.
SB 157—LS 6545/DI 154

January 16, 2026
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
SENATE BILL No. 157
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
insurance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 27-1-24.6-6, AS ADDED BY P.L.216-2025,
2 SECTION 41, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. (a) A health plan must provide the amount of
4 the national average drug acquisition cost for a generic drug to the plan
5 sponsor.
6 (b) A pharmacist (as defined in IC 27-1-24.5-9) or pharmacy (as
7 defined in IC 27-1-24.5-11) must provide the amount of the
8 national average drug acquisition cost for a generic drug on the
9 written materials provided to an individual at the point of sale of
10 the generic drug.
